## [Mechanisms of evolutionary change]{style="font-family:Comic Sans MS;font-weight:normal;"} {background='imgs/paper-bg.jpg'}

<br><br>

:::: {.columns}

::: {.column width='50%'}

- Genetic drift
- Migration
- Mutation
- Recombination
- Selection

:::

::: {.column width='50%'}

- [Goal]{style='color:red;'}: To connect the knowledge of the mechanisms of evolution with the patterns observed across the tree of life, and those observed within and among populations

:::

::::



# [Outline]{style="font-family:Comic Sans MS;font-weight:normal;"} {background='imgs/paper-bg.jpg'}

- [Story 1:]{style='color:red;'} Macroclimatic and maternal effects on the evolution of reproductive traits in lizards
- [Story 2:]{style='color:red;'} The correlated evolution of foraging mode and reproductive effort in lizards
- [Story 3:]{style='color:red;'} Geographic and seasonal variation of the for gene reveal signatures of local adaptation in *Drosophila melanogaster*
- [Story 4:]{style='color:red;'} Foraging actively can be advantageous in heterogeneous environments


