## [Results]{style='font-family:Comic Sans MS,sans-serif;font-weight:normal;'} {background='imgs/paper-bg.jpg'}

A model describing a direct and an indirect [effect of precipitation]{style='color:red;'} on the evolution of reproductive traits was strongly supported


:::: {.colums}

::: {.column width='30%'}

<font size='5'>PP: primary production</font><br>
<font size='5'>PR: precipitation</font><br>
<font size='5'>BT: body temperature</font><br>
<font size='5'>FS: female size</font><br>
<font size='5'>HS: hatchling size</font><br>
<font size='5'>CS: clutch size</font><br>
<font size='5'> [Blue]{style='color:blue;'} and [red]{style='color:red;'} arrows represent positive and negative effetcs, respectively.</font>

:::

